ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v24.group

Class PEX_P07_PEX_CAUSE

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractStructure
      • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractGroup
        • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v24.group.PEX_P07_PEX_CAUSE
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Group, Structure, Visitable, Serializable

    public class PEX_P07_PEX_CAUSE
extends AbstractGroup

    Represents a PEX_P07_PEX_CAUSE group structure (a Group object). A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in/excluded together. This Group contains the following elements:

    • 1: PCR (Possible Causal Relationship)
    • 2: PEX_P07_RX_ORDER (a Group object) optional
    • 3: PEX_P07_RX_ADMINISTRATION (a Group object) optional repeating
    • 4: PRB (Problem Details) optional repeating
    • 5: OBX (Observation/Result) optional repeating
    • 6: NTE (Notes and Comments) optional repeating
    • 7: PEX_P07_ASSOCIATED_PERSON (a Group object) optional
    • 8: PEX_P07_STUDY (a Group object) optional repeating
    See Also:
